"children":[
"Diagnosis and Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ba74b4",
"children":[
"Immunocompetent persons with primary infection are usually asymptomatic, but latent infection may persist, and reactivation of the infection is a risk if the person becomes immunocompromised. Look for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b51b04",
"children":[
"encephalitis, chorioretinitis, or pneumonitis in immunocompromised patients"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"775c6a",
"children":[
"any focal neurologic syndrome, acute or subacute"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"223a34",
"children":[
"mononucleosis-like syndrome"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_id_s41_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"23e1da",
"children":[
"Select IgG serologic testing in patients with suspected toxoplasmosis and brain MRI for neurologic signs and symptoms. Typical findings on imaging include multiple ring-enhancing lesions."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s41_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c59cf8",
"children":[
"Select empiric treatment with sulfadiazine, pyrimethamine, and folic acid in patients with multiple ring-enhancing lesions, positive ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Toxoplasma gondii"
]
},
" serologic test results (IgG), and immune suppression (CD4 cell count <200/μL). Biopsy lesions that fail to respond to 2 weeks of empiric therapy."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_id_f18"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
}
]
},
