"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Lymphoma (primary ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"central nervous system",
"children":[
"CNS"
]
},
","
]
},
" B-cell lymphoma)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a33a9e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Often a solitary lesion is located in the periventricular or periependymal area or in the corpus callosum"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ab94c4",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Neither clinical nor neuroradiologic findings reliably distinguish lymphoma from toxoplasmosis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9bf2ea",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Brain biopsy is diagnostic"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
